Pratyush Banerjee wrote:

&gt;    Hi All,

&gt; 

&gt; I have been working with Heritrix-2.0.0 code for sometime. However i 

&gt; have just written a custom WriterProcessor

&gt; wherein in the initialTasks() i need to get the value for the 

&gt; &quot;max-toe-threads&quot; as set in the global sheet.

&gt; 

&gt; I can access the default value but not the live value whichever way i 

&gt; try. The standard method of global.get() does not

&gt; work since it requires an object instead of the class.

&gt; 

&gt; It would be of great help if somebody can suggest me a method.



MAX_TOE_THREADS is a setting on CrawlControllerImpl, so you&#39;d need an 

instance of that to pass into:



context.get(controller, CrawlControllerImpl.MAX_TOE_THREADS);



To ensure your processor has such a reference, you should be able to use 

the same technique as used by the RuntimeLimitEnforcer -- an 

autoreference to the CrawlControllerImpl as part of its own settings:



final public static Key&lt;CrawlControllerImpl&gt; CONTROLLER =

         Key.makeAuto(CrawlControllerImpl.class);



...then in initialTasks()...



CrawlControllerImpl c = curi.get(this, CONTROLLER);

     int toes = context.get(c, CrawlControllerImpl.MAX_TOE_THREADS);



I haven&#39;t tried this, but think it will do what you need.



- Gordon @ IA



















